com.nokia.maps.map

Interface MapListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GestureMapCanvas, MapCanvas

    public interface MapListener
    This interface defines a series of callback method to use when rendering a map. The MapDisplay informs its client of map updates through the MapListener interface.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onMapContentComplete()
      This method is called when the map content is completely present and all objects have been rendered.
      void onMapContentUpdated()
      This method is called when the content of the map is updated and client should therefore update the screen.
      void onMapUpdateError(java.lang.String description, java.lang.Throwable detail, boolean critical)
      This method is called by the implementation in the case of error.

    • Method Detail

      • onMapContentComplete

        void onMapContentComplete()
        This method is called when the map content is completely present and all objects have been rendered. A standard implementation need not do anything here, but this callback may be used for determining when a map is no longer in the process of updating.

      • onMapContentUpdated

        void onMapContentUpdated()
        This method is called when the content of the map is updated and client should therefore update the screen.

      • onMapUpdateError

        void onMapUpdateError(java.lang.String description,
                    java.lang.Throwable detail,
                    boolean critical)
        This method is called by the implementation in the case of error.
        Parameters:
        description - short description of the error
        detail - the error occurred
        critical - true if the background worker cannot handle the error situation and continue execution, false if the error is potentially recoverable.
